claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table showing vaccine effectiveness (VE, % with 95% CI) for two vaccine types (RIV4 and SD-IIV4) in age groups 18–64 years and ≥65 years, with subgroups by sex, risk condition, and influenza season. does not support the claim because the table only presents vaccine effectiveness data and does not provide any information on HA microgram content per strain
